editorialSummary.text: American restaurant & bar notable for its prime lakeside setting in the middle of Central Park.

originalText.text: Loeb Boathouse in Central Park offers a magical experience with its boat rentals that extend until sundown. The restaurant is momentarily closed but they have a outside deck by the rental boat stand. Despite the long 2-hour wait, the romantic boat ride is a once-in-a-lifetime experience. Maneuvering the paddle requires minimal skills, allowing you to explore the lake. The panoramic view of New York from the water is breathtaking. While the boats show signs of aging and could use renewal, the overall experience is undeniably worthwhile.

originalText.text: Row-boating down the lake. Romantic? You bet your sunscreen it was. Every time we tried on a weekend, the line was incredibly long. But we plotted a master plan: a Monday escape during lunch break. We power walked to the lakeside, two adventurers on a lunchtime quest. The line? Nonexistent. No wait, no hassle. The boat seats 4 people, even though it was just the 2 of us on our romantic escapade. Twenty bucks for an hour of aqua daydream. It was nice to see the turtles swimming about, getting their sun tan on. My boyfriend had his duty and I had mine, making sure I captured everything in videos and selfies for our memories. Nothing too wild or outlandish, but let's be honest – this was no ordinary afternoon. Tourists or locals would benefit from this adventure at least once in a lifetime. It is a go from us!

originalText.text:
The Loeb Boathouse in Central Park, New York City, is a popular spot for renting boats. They offer rowboats and pedal boats for visitors to enjoy a leisurely ride on the lake. It's a wonderful activity, especially during the warmer months when you can enjoy the beautiful scenery of Central Park.  A waiver is required--they need to post bigger sign and remind people they need  to complete while waiting in line.
** I would recommend weekday to avoid wait in long line.

originalText.text:
The Central Park Boathouse is an iconic attraction of Central Park and a must visit dining destination of New York City.

In August of 2023, I brought and treated my wife and myself for dinner at the Central Park Boathouse and we very much enjoyed our dining experience.

The wait time went by fairly quickly and our meal was served within a few minutes of seating down at our table.

Both my wife and I very much enjoyed our hamburger and fries meal because we found that it was well cooked and superbly delicious!!!

When visiting Central Park, both my wife and I highly recommend that you visit and dine at the Central Park Boathouse!!!

originalText.text:
great experience, went there with family, the dinner starts at 6pm, it was a super hot day so we set indoors and still it was a bit hot but worked, our server was very sweet and she suggested the best things, loved the service and the setup indoors is very cool.
we had few drinks and mostly 3 dishes, the quantity is okay not to small or huge, the place is not even that expensive too.
my favorite was Elderflower Cosmopolitan,
and they had special of the day was cold tomato soup which was something new but really liked it, had the mule, cucumber cooler and beer. everything i loved it.
in food we had the tomato soup with bread, red pasta and miso grilled king oyster mushrooms. it was delightful and the vibe was calming. loved it.
happy vibe. :)
